[link: /commands/docs/str_camel-case.md] ``str camel-case``
Convert a string to camelCase.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_capitalize.md] ``str capitalize``
Capitalize the first letter of text.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_contains.md] ``str contains``
Checks if string input contains a substring.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_distance.md] ``str distance``
Compare two strings and return the edit distance/Levenshtein distance.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_downcase.md] ``str downcase``
Convert text to lowercase.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_ends-with.md] ``str ends-with``
Check if an input ends with a string.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_escape-regex.md] ``str escape-regex``
Escapes special characters in the input string with '
\'.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_expand.md] ``str expand``
Generates all possible combinations defined in brace expansion syntax.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_index-of.md] ``str index-of``
Returns start index of first occurrence of string in input, or -1 if no match.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_join.md] ``str join``
Concatenate multiple strings into a single string, with an optional separator between each.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_kebab-case.md] ``str kebab-case``
Convert a string to kebab-case.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_length.md] ``str length``
Output the length of any strings in the pipeline.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_pascal-case.md] ``str pascal-case``
Convert a string to PascalCase.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_replace.md] ``str replace``
Find and replace text in the input string.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_reverse.md] ``str reverse``
Reverse every string in the pipeline.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_screaming-snake-case.md] ``str screaming-snake-case``
Convert a string to SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_snake-case.md] ``str snake-case``
Convert a string to snake_case.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_starts-with.md] ``str starts-with``
Check if an input starts with a string.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_stats.md] ``str stats``
Gather word count statistics on the text.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_substring.md] ``str substring``
Get part of a string. Note that the first character of a string is index 0.
built-in
[link: /commands/docs/str_title-case.md] ``str title-case``
Convert a string to Title Case.
built-in
